Text.Value: Damn it, Philomeen. After all that's happened.
Please - I'm working as fast as I can.
I was right about you. Drugnin' monster. You... you...

EditorData.NodeContext: Breaks down into tears after line
EditorData.logicalname: Told her you would kill Philomeen earlier

Text.Value: Move on? I gave her everything. And she has the gall to send you to break me?
We've got to leave Grymforge. Beldron must have a plan.
May Ironhand be with her.
Philomeen is - gone.
Blow the wall open. Or don't. I don't care anymore.
Bad news, I'm afraid. Philomeen is done for.

EditorData.logicalname: Lie: Already met Philomeen and she is alive

Text.Value: At least... at least some of us are safe, praise Ironhand.
You got the smokepowder? Go on, blow the rubble.
Monster. Get away from me.

EditorData.logicalname: Said you plan to kill Philomeen

Text.Value: Philomeen is gone.
Get us out of here. All of us. And hope for her sake her path never crosses mine again.
You should crush that drow's skull for what he's done to us. Wouldn't dream of standing in your way.
If only there were more blessings to count.
Phil... it can't be...

EditorData.NodeContext: Sad beyond belief; said to herself
EditorData.logicalname: Shared that her lover was dead or lover has left her after gnomes were freed

Text.Value: Just get away from me.
What? No. No - it can't be. That's not... that's not... *sob*

Text.Value: Magga Cammara - you offed the bastards.
Gods no. It wasn't supposed... to be like this...
I found Philomeen. And she wants you to move on.

Synopsis: One of the gnomes who the duergar have enslaved. She's hard at work trying to free the True Soul trapped with the other gnomes. Her lover has fled the scene; player might share the news that the lover is dead, or has rejected her.
